{
  "texts": [
    "If neither party fully controls an AI system, the question arises of who should bear responsibility for harm.",
    "Autonomous features in AI products can limit users' ability to prevent harm while using the product.",
    "For example, accidents involving autonomous vehicles are less likely to result from driver errors and more likely to be caused by product defects (Kim, 2017).",
    "In the case of conventional cars, consumers are in control when using them.",
    "However, when it comes to autonomous AI systems, users are not actively involved in their operation."
  ]
}